## Why RL Learns Passive Play

The root cause is the reward signal. In a game where ships on your planets count as final score, an RL agent quickly learns that **not sending ships out is safe** — you can't lose ships you don't dispatch. A fleet sent out can be destroyed, intercepted, or arrive too late. A fleet kept home definitely counts at turn 500.

So the agent converges on a strategy of "hoard ships, only attack when obviously free" — which looks like lots of no-ops and conservative dispatching. It's reward hacking the scoring function.

